---
name: "Feature template"
description: "Standard files when adding a new feature."
globs: ["app/renderer/src/ts/features/**/*", "app/renderer/src/views/**/*"]
alwaysApply: true
---

When creating a new feature `<name>`:

1) Create `app/renderer/src/ts/features/<name>/` with files:
   - `types.ts`
   - `service.ts`
   - `store.ts`
2) Create a view file under `app/renderer/src/views/` as needed (e.g., `NameView.svelte`).
3) Use aliases for imports (e.g., `@features/<name>/store`).
4) Wire the view in `App.svelte` (or via router later).